posts.post_title: WTT: T206 SGC for The Doors CD Box Set SOLD!
posts.post_content: I would like to trade this 7 CD Box Set of The Doors Complete Studio Recordings for a 50 -60 SGC graded T206. I was going to list it on ebay and then use the proceeds for a card purchase but figured I'd thow it out there and see if the fish were biting. CD's are like new and included all inserts and booklet. Again, I hope this isn't too weird of an offer. If so, feel free to delete this posting.

This is the end my special friend; the end.

Good luck trying to find a trade partner; cool idea. ;)

Relax, take it as it comes.

Well Tony, I'll "walk the thin line" for you in regards to a response. It is obvious that you are trying to build a baseball card "Empire" with your trade request. Well, "I'll be the best I can" in regards to crafting a response. 

First time visitors to Net54 who view your thread might think, "People are strange" for posting such a request. But then they will think about the request and "Tell All the People" about this great idea. 

Personally, I was glad to see the request. The love of my life, "Maggie M'Gill" left me last night..for a woman from LA. I was pretty upset so "I was going to the roadhouse to have a real good time" but they didn't open for a few more hours. But, with time to kill before the bar opened, I thought of a woman in my office, I think her name is "Della Brown," who is quite cute so I might pursue her.

Do you think it would be too forward if I walked up to her and said, "Hello, I love you won't you tell me your name?"

Concerning the trade of the boxvset, I'll take "5 to 1" odds that you don't find any takers.
